            "title": "Introduction to Rational Numbers",
            "readingTime": 5,
            "content": "# Rational Numbers\n\nA rational number is a number that can be expressed as p/q where p and q are integers and q ≠ 0.\n\n## Examples\n- 1/2, 3/4, -5/7\n- All integers are rational (can be written as n/1)"
        },
        {
            "id": "l2",
            "title": "Operations on Rational Numbers",
            "readingTime": 6,
            "content": "# Operations\n\n## Addition and Subtraction\n- Find LCM of denominators\n- Convert to equivalent fractions\n- Add or subtract numerators\n\n## Multiplication and Division\n- Multiply numerators and denominators\n- For division, multiply by reciprocal"
        }
